<title>USA: U.S. mortgage application volume rose in latest wk.</title>
<headline>U.S. mortgage application volume rose in latest wk.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The volume of U.S. mortgage applications rose 1.8 percent in the week ended May 2, according to a Mortgage Bankers Association of America weekly survey.</p>
<p>Specifically, the volume of applications to refinance mortgages rose 6.1 percent in the latest survey week, while applications to purchase mortgages rose 0.9 percent.</p>
<p>The seasonally adjusted refinancing index rose 6.1 percent to 289.6 from 273.2 the previous week.</p>
<p>The purchase index rose 0.9 percent to 189.4 in the latest survey from 187.7 in the previous week.  </p>
